body:
Great - glad  you are having a go at this :-)

Apart from the config changes you'll need to set up the internals in `fs/sync/sync.go`

Here is where rclone sets up the backupDir

https://github.com/ncw/rclone/blob/eb4125376482206505bc9521408a5b58ad074c2b/fs/sync/sync.go#L108-L128

I think you want to add something like this on the end at line 128

```go
} else if fs.Config.Suffix != "" {
		// --backup-dir is not set but --suffix is - use the destination as the backupDir
		s.backupDir = fdst
		s.suffix = fs.Config.Suffix
		if !operations.CanServerSideMove(s.backupDir) {
			return nil, fserrors.FatalError(errors.New("can't use --suffix on a remote which doesn't support server side move or copy"))
		}
}
```

And that may be enough!

This will need a new test.  You may be able to modify the existing one

https://github.com/ncw/rclone/blob/eb4125376482206505bc9521408a5b58ad074c2b/fs/sync/sync_test.go#L1082

Let me know if you need more help :-)
